cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SD 

The paper deals with the use of convolutional neural networks for segmenting neurons and detecting synapses in electron microscopy images. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of heuristics and prior biological knowledge, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with the reconstruction of a connectome, which could fall under the scientific computing (cs.SD) sub-category.
